Exoplanets in the HD 93083 system


HD 93083 b

HD 93083 b was discovered by the La Silla Observatory observatory, in 2005-07, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.48 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 93083 b is 117.660 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 93083 b is 13.400 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 93083 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
